Package view

package view
Contains classes responsible for displaying the user interface.

This package is responsible for rendering all visual components of the application and presenting them to the user. It includes components for displaying menus, appointment details, medical records, and other user interface elements.

Key classes in this package:

  • AdminDisplayMenu - display menu for admin object
  • AppointmentOutcomeRecordDisplay - Displays detailed outcomes of appointments
  • AppointmentsDisplay - Shows a list of scheduled appointments
  • AvailableDatesDisplay - Displays dates available for appointments
  • DayChecker -validating the day of date
  • DayDisplay - Displays a day of date
  • Display - A generic display class serving as the base for other UI components
  • DisplayGender - Displays gender options
  • DisplayInbox - Displays messages or notifications for users
  • DisplayInfo - A generic class for information display
  • DisplayLog - Displays logs from system
  • DisplayMenu - A generic class for menu display
  • DisplayPrompt - Shows prompts to guide users in making selections or entering information
  • DoctorDisplayMenu - Displays a menu specific to Doctor object
  • DoctorRateDisplay - display rating system for a Doctor
  • DoctorRatingDisplay - displays doctors to be rated
  • EmailUpdateDisplay - Displays a prompt for updating user email addresses in their profile
  • Input - A generic class for handling user input
  • InputDayChoice - Allows the user to input or select a specific day
  • InputEmail - Handles email input from users, including validation and formatting checks
  • InputID - prompt an input for ID
  • InputInt - prompt an input for an INT choice
  • InputIntChoice - Allows users to choose from a range of integer options
  • InputMonthChoice - Provides a selection interface for months
  • InputPassword - Facilitates input of passwords with basic validation
  • InputPasswordStrict - Handles password input with stricter requirements
  • InputPrescriptionChoice - Allows selection of prescription options
  • InputString - Handles string input from users
  • InputTimeChoice - Provides an interface for selecting specific times, used in scheduling or appointments.
  • InventoryDisplay - Displays the current inventory of items for admin or pharmacist review.
  • InventoryDisplayMenu - Provides a menu for navigating inventory-related features like stock updates or replenishment requests.
  • MedicalRecordDisplay - Displays detailed medical records for patients
  • MedicineDisplay - Shows details about medicines
  • MonthDisplay - Display a list of months in a selection menu format.
  • PatientDisplayMenu - Provides a menu interface for patients to view their appointments, medical records, and more.
  • PharmacistDisplayMenu - Displays a menu for pharmacists to manage prescriptions, inventory, and patient interactions.
  • PrescriptionDisplay - Displays prescription details
  • ReplenishmentRequestMenu - Displays a menu for managing replenishment requests for inventory items.
  • RoleDisplayMenu - Allows selection or display of user roles
  • StaffDisplay - Displays information about staff members
  • StaffMDisplayMenu - Provides a menu for managing staff
  • TimeDisplay - Displays specific times
  • invalid reference 
    view.UpdatePrescriptionStatusMenu
    - Displays a menu for updating the status of prescriptions

Since:
1.0
Author:
Adam Soh
